<L>__{interior public house. the past. evening.}
<A>__{the george and dragon on a saturday night. the air loud with laughter and thick with pipe smoke. clodhoppers crowd the snug, many of them roaring drunk, with their florid complexions, stained and broken teeth. darwin trying, to slip in discreetly is spied by a group of locals who hail him and gather around him, wedging him into a corner with their overloud loud talk and laughter.}
<C>__{thatcher}
<D>__{mr darwin! mr darwin! i was explaining to mr goodman here your interest in breeding. mr darwin is our foremost scholar in the village.}
<C>__{darwin}
<D>__{no. no i am but one of many. there is squire lubbock, and the reverend innes}
<A>__{the thatcher waves them away as lesser talents.}
